info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 08 at 2:09AM MST until January 10 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM TUESDAY TO 2 PM MST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 55 mph with gusts up to 80 mph expected. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County, South Laramie Range and South Laramie Range Foothills. * WHEN...From 5 AM Tuesday to 2 PM MST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage. The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
